<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880602-0103 </DOCNO><HL> Corrections andamp; Amplifications: Bell Atlantic Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> USW PAC BLS BEL NYN SBC AIT </CO><IN> TEL </IN><TEXT>   BELL ATLANTIC Corp. doesn't plan to ban dial-a-porn services on its telephone network unless ordered to do so by regulators or the courts. The company will rely instead on a proposed call-blocking feature that would be available at the customer's option. In an earlier edition, the company was incorrectly described as continuing to consider whether to ban such services.    (See: &quot;U S West to Ban 'Dial-a-Porn' Services On Its Network; Other Bells May Follow&quot; -- WSJ May 31, 1988)</TEXT></DOC>